WEBVTT

00:01.044 --> 00:03.438
Grandpa:
Hi, Silas.

00:03.481 --> 00:07.007
This is your birthday tape
from Pappy and Grammy.

00:07.050 --> 00:12.447
We love you very much
and miss you tons, kiddo.

00:13.448 --> 00:17.104
We're just so excited
that you're 6 years old now.

00:17.147 --> 00:19.454
Where did the time go?

00:19.497 --> 00:22.935
[Muffled indistinct
conversations]

00:22.979 --> 00:26.374
♪♪

00:26.417 --> 00:29.377
Grandma: We want you to know
you're special, Silas.

00:29.420 --> 00:32.075
You're a sweet, thoughtful,
caring young man,

00:32.119 --> 00:36.297
and we're so proud to have you
as our grandson.

00:36.340 --> 00:39.517
[Voice echoing]

00:39.561 --> 00:41.911
Hope: Hey, sleepy heads.
Wake the hell up!

00:41.954 --> 00:44.609
[Fires crackling,
walkers growling in distance]

00:44.653 --> 00:46.176
Hope?

00:49.310 --> 00:51.051
Hope, where are you?

00:51.094 --> 00:53.966
Take a guess.
We're doing Elton's plan.

00:54.010 --> 00:56.056
No, we're not.
You are not.

00:56.099 --> 00:58.623
Hope: I can get to the factoryand sound the siren,

00:58.667 --> 01:00.408
clear a pathfor you guys to get through.

01:00.451 --> 01:04.629
It's your best chanceof making it out alive.

01:04.673 --> 01:06.240
♪♪

01:06.283 --> 01:08.242
We don't even know
if the siren works

01:08.285 --> 01:10.548
or if
we can get it to work.

01:10.592 --> 01:13.421
We weren't gonna risk anyone
on this.

01:13.464 --> 01:15.901
We decided.You decided.

01:15.945 --> 01:18.252
Hope,
just come back, please.

01:18.295 --> 01:19.514
Chill, okay?

01:19.557 --> 01:21.690
I-It's not even all that baddown here --

01:21.733 --> 01:24.127
at least not comparedto your cooking.

01:24.171 --> 01:25.476
[Coughing]

01:25.520 --> 01:27.435
We will find another way.
Just come back.

01:27.478 --> 01:29.263
We knew what was up
when we left,

01:29.306 --> 01:31.482
how it would be,but we did it for Dad.

01:31.526 --> 01:32.918
This,
it should be me.

01:32.962 --> 01:34.268
It has to be.

01:34.311 --> 01:36.226
Oh, shit.
I-I got to go.

01:36.270 --> 01:38.141
[Radio crackling]Hope.

01:38.185 --> 01:41.449
Are you there?
Hope?

01:41.492 --> 01:43.886
Hope. Hope!

01:43.929 --> 01:49.892
♪♪

01:54.157 --> 01:56.681
We're glad
you're here, Silas,

01:56.725 --> 01:58.553
and we're glad your uncle
decided to sponsor you.

01:58.596 --> 02:00.729
Now, you know
what that means, right?

02:00.772 --> 02:02.296
[Paper rustles]

02:02.339 --> 02:05.125
It means
you get a fresh start.

02:05.168 --> 02:06.909
Hey.

02:07.997 --> 02:10.608
Omaha is pretty great,
okay?

02:10.652 --> 02:14.917
But this place,
it's big without being too big.

02:16.440 --> 02:19.313
Now, I understand
that you, uh --

02:19.356 --> 02:22.229
you want to work with your unclehere in the physical plant

02:22.272 --> 02:24.448
instead of
going to school?

02:24.492 --> 02:26.320
Yeah,
Silas here is...

02:26.363 --> 02:28.757
he's the hardest worker
you ever want to meet.

02:28.800 --> 02:31.673
Look, if you ever do
change your mind, Silas,

02:31.716 --> 02:34.545
school is always an option
for you, alright?

02:34.589 --> 02:37.200
Monument High's a great,
great way

02:37.244 --> 02:38.723
to meet people
your age.

02:38.767 --> 02:41.378
Well, he -- he appreciates
the opportunity.

02:41.422 --> 02:44.947
We both do.

02:44.990 --> 02:49.212
♪♪

02:49.256 --> 02:50.605
He's a good kid.

02:50.648 --> 02:53.738
No matter what anyone says,
he's a good kid.

02:53.782 --> 03:00.223
♪♪

03:00.267 --> 03:02.834
[Walkers growling in distance]

03:02.878 --> 03:04.532
Iris:
Hope? Hope?

03:04.575 --> 03:05.881
Hope,
are you there?

03:05.924 --> 03:07.491
Hope: Sorry, things got hairyfor a sec.

03:07.535 --> 03:08.927
Jesus.

03:08.971 --> 03:11.495
Listen, I'm in an office
in front of the factory.

03:11.539 --> 03:13.758
It's a straight shot
from the entrance --

03:13.802 --> 03:15.499
not too many empties.

03:15.543 --> 03:17.893
From here, I can use a siren
to clear a path to the exit.

03:17.936 --> 03:19.329
We're on the way.
Just stay there.

03:19.373 --> 03:20.939
That's the thing.

03:20.983 --> 03:22.332
I'll be gone by the time
you get here. Just get here.

03:22.376 --> 03:24.291
Stay put,
wait till you hear the sirens,

03:24.334 --> 03:25.814
and make a run
for the exit.

03:25.857 --> 03:27.207
I'll meet you there.

03:27.250 --> 03:28.860
No, just stay thereand I'll go with you.

03:28.904 --> 03:30.993
I will move faster
and quieter alone.

03:31.036 --> 03:32.255
You need to trust me.

03:32.299 --> 03:34.126
Hope.

03:34.170 --> 03:36.172
Iris.
Do you trust me or not?

03:36.216 --> 03:39.697
[Growling continues]

03:39.741 --> 03:42.222
♪♪

03:42.265 --> 03:43.919
Yes.

03:43.962 --> 03:45.703
Good.

03:45.747 --> 03:47.096
I'm gonna have to turn off
my walkie until it's safe.

03:47.139 --> 03:48.619
In the meantime,

03:48.663 --> 03:50.055
you're gonna do exactly
as I'm telling you to do.

03:50.099 --> 03:52.580
Got it?
[Sighs]

03:52.623 --> 03:55.147
Iris!
Yes.

03:55.191 --> 03:56.975
Okay, I'll do it.
Awesome.

03:57.019 --> 03:58.977
And, Iris,
just one more thing.

03:59.021 --> 04:00.805
What?

04:00.849 --> 04:02.720
Grin, girl.

04:02.764 --> 04:04.592
I love you.

04:04.635 --> 04:09.597
♪♪

04:09.640 --> 04:11.599
[Sniffles]
I'm grinning.

04:11.642 --> 04:14.689
No, you're flipping me off
through the talkie.

04:14.732 --> 04:17.213
♪♪

04:17.257 --> 04:18.475
[Sniffles]

04:18.519 --> 04:20.825
I'm grinning.

04:20.869 --> 04:22.436
Good.

04:22.479 --> 04:27.963
♪♪

04:28.006 --> 04:30.313
[Walkers growling]

04:30.357 --> 04:38.147
♪♪

04:38.190 --> 04:39.888
Elton:
I can see the office.

04:39.931 --> 04:42.282
It's a straight shot,
just like she said.

04:42.325 --> 04:43.848
Most of the empties
are being attracted

04:43.892 --> 04:45.328
by the fires on either side,

04:45.372 --> 04:48.592
but we might still
bump into a few.

04:48.636 --> 04:50.290
We should go now.

04:50.333 --> 04:54.990
[Growling continues]

04:55.033 --> 05:05.000
♪♪

05:05.043 --> 05:10.092
♪♪

05:10.135 --> 05:12.747
I hope we don't have to
kill any,

05:12.790 --> 05:15.097
but in case we do,

05:15.140 --> 05:18.100
do you think
you can do it?

05:18.143 --> 05:24.585
♪♪

05:24.628 --> 05:29.546
Uh, I'll carry all your bags
so you can kill --

05:29.590 --> 05:31.418
so you both can.

05:31.461 --> 05:33.420
♪♪

05:33.463 --> 05:35.509
I mean,
I'm strong.

05:35.552 --> 05:36.988
It's the best I can doright now,

05:37.032 --> 05:40.427
and we'll go faster
this way.

05:45.867 --> 05:48.435
Let's go.

05:48.478 --> 05:52.134
♪♪

05:52.177 --> 05:54.049
[Walkers growling]

05:54.092 --> 06:03.580
♪♪

06:03.624 --> 06:07.018
[Wind whistling,
fires crackling]

06:12.894 --> 06:22.860
♪♪

06:22.904 --> 06:32.870
♪♪

06:32.914 --> 06:42.271
♪♪

06:42.314 --> 06:44.273
♪♪

06:44.316 --> 06:45.492
[Growling]

06:45.535 --> 06:55.502
♪♪

06:55.545 --> 06:57.504
[Grunts]

06:57.547 --> 06:59.506
♪♪

06:59.549 --> 07:01.203
[Grunts]

07:01.246 --> 07:04.554
[Growling continues]

07:04.598 --> 07:08.993
♪♪

07:09.037 --> 07:11.909
Silas!

07:11.953 --> 07:16.218
♪♪

07:16.261 --> 07:18.786
Let's go.

07:18.829 --> 07:20.570
♪♪

07:20.614 --> 07:25.445
[Walkers growling]

07:25.488 --> 07:35.455
♪♪

07:35.498 --> 07:39.633
[Coughing]

07:43.071 --> 07:46.378
[Breathes deeply]

07:47.467 --> 07:50.078
Iris: Hey.

07:50.121 --> 07:51.514
You okay?

07:51.558 --> 07:54.256
Just got turned around.

07:54.299 --> 07:56.345
That's all.

08:03.526 --> 08:06.573
Till we hear from Hope,
we should check this place out,

08:06.616 --> 08:08.836
see if there's anything
we can use --

08:08.879 --> 08:10.968
weapons,
food, anything.

08:11.012 --> 08:13.449
Roger that.

08:18.846 --> 08:22.850
[Growling continues]

08:22.893 --> 08:32.860
♪♪

08:32.903 --> 08:39.954
♪♪

08:39.997 --> 08:43.392
[Walkers growling]

08:53.315 --> 08:56.274
♪♪

08:56.318 --> 08:59.321
[Flashlight clicks]

08:59.364 --> 09:09.331
♪♪

09:09.374 --> 09:11.638
♪♪

09:11.681 --> 09:14.902
[Electricity crackles,
flashlight clicking rapidly]

09:14.945 --> 09:24.912
♪♪

09:24.955 --> 09:27.131
♪♪

09:27.175 --> 09:31.135
[Electricity crackles,
flashlight clicking rapidly]

09:31.179 --> 09:32.746
♪♪

09:32.789 --> 09:36.358
Shit.

09:36.401 --> 09:39.187
[Items clattering]

09:39.230 --> 09:42.233
[Walker growling]

09:42.277 --> 09:51.373
♪♪

09:51.416 --> 09:53.636
♪♪

10:05.648 --> 10:07.998
What's up?

10:09.086 --> 10:12.437
My momused to buy me these.

10:12.481 --> 10:16.616
I used to ask her to
back in Omaha --

10:16.659 --> 10:19.357
you know, b-before.

10:19.401 --> 10:21.446
You miss her?

10:21.490 --> 10:22.839
No.

10:29.672 --> 10:31.021
Sometimes.

10:31.065 --> 10:33.023
You miss yours?

10:34.242 --> 10:36.940
Every day.

10:40.857 --> 10:43.512
So, what was that
out there?

10:43.555 --> 10:47.690
♪♪

10:47.734 --> 10:49.474
It's okay
if you're scared.

10:49.518 --> 10:52.434
I'm not.

10:52.477 --> 10:55.176
Not of...them.

10:55.219 --> 10:57.744
♪♪

10:57.787 --> 10:59.833
Hey, Silas, can you give me
a hand over here?

10:59.876 --> 11:02.531
Seems this door's stuck.

11:12.715 --> 11:15.370
[Grunts]

11:15.413 --> 11:17.415
Oh!
[Gasps]

11:17.459 --> 11:18.721
Hey, relax!
It's me.

11:18.765 --> 11:20.114
Felix!

11:20.157 --> 11:21.898
Hi.
Hi.

11:21.942 --> 11:23.508
Hi. [Chuckles]

11:23.552 --> 11:24.858
Are --
Are you okay?

11:24.901 --> 11:26.381
Where's Hope?

11:26.424 --> 11:29.993
♪♪

11:30.037 --> 11:31.821
Where the hell's Hope?

11:31.865 --> 11:34.345
Felix: Iris?

11:34.389 --> 11:35.695
Hmm?

11:37.827 --> 11:40.961
Wait, wait, wait, wait. Soyou're telling me that this wasall your idea and not Hope's?

11:41.004 --> 11:42.310
I talked her into it.

11:44.660 --> 11:47.707
So it was one of you twothat left the breadcrumbs?

11:47.750 --> 11:48.969
Bread--
What breadcrumbs?

11:49.012 --> 11:50.535
The can of peaches
on the street,

11:50.579 --> 11:52.015
the graffiti --

11:52.059 --> 11:54.148
the trail one of you left behindto get us here.

11:54.191 --> 11:56.498
No.
She didn't leave those.

11:56.541 --> 11:57.804
She wouldn't.
She?

11:57.847 --> 12:00.241
She -- You're telling methat was Hope?

12:00.284 --> 12:02.634
I'm saying it couldn't have beenon purpose.

12:02.678 --> 12:04.724
She wants to find Dad
as much as I do.

12:04.767 --> 12:06.638
Will you just tell uswhere she is,

12:06.682 --> 12:08.684
where the siren is
she's going for?

12:08.728 --> 12:09.903
I can't.

12:09.946 --> 12:13.515
Iris, you're smarterthan this, okay?

12:13.558 --> 12:17.084
This is Hope's lifethat we're talking about.

12:17.127 --> 12:19.303
And if I tell you
where she is,

12:19.347 --> 12:22.045
then you and Huck go after her
and get yourselves killed.

12:22.089 --> 12:24.091
There's a plan.

12:24.134 --> 12:26.310
This part of it's hers.

12:26.354 --> 12:29.270
I hate it, but right now
it's our best chance

12:29.313 --> 12:30.619
of getting
out of here alive.

12:30.662 --> 12:32.403
You're just gonna have to
trust her,

12:32.447 --> 12:33.840
like the rest of us.

12:33.883 --> 12:36.407
Hate to say it,
kid's got a point.

12:36.451 --> 12:38.975
There's a crowd of uglies
incoming.

12:39.019 --> 12:40.760
Without some kind
of distraction,

12:40.803 --> 12:43.327
we ain't
getting out of here.

12:43.371 --> 12:47.549
♪♪

12:47.592 --> 12:49.159
Hey. Don't worry.
Okay?

12:49.203 --> 12:51.422
We -- We can stillget out of this. It's not over.

12:51.466 --> 12:53.773
And then what?

12:53.816 --> 12:55.122
♪♪

12:55.165 --> 12:57.341
I know
how it's gonna go now,

12:57.385 --> 12:59.996
how it always goes.

13:00.040 --> 13:02.042
♪♪

13:02.085 --> 13:04.305
[Muffled industrial-rock music
plays]

13:04.348 --> 13:08.352
♪♪

13:08.396 --> 13:10.833
Shh.
Let's go.

13:10.877 --> 13:20.843
♪♪

13:20.887 --> 13:30.853
♪♪

13:30.897 --> 13:37.817
♪♪

13:37.860 --> 13:39.209
Oh, hi.

13:39.253 --> 13:41.255
Hi.

13:41.298 --> 13:44.258
This is my dad's lab.

13:44.301 --> 13:47.870
I left
my English Lit homework here.

13:47.914 --> 13:50.830
I'll get
out of your hair.

13:56.879 --> 13:59.490
See you around.

14:04.234 --> 14:05.714
He left a week ago

14:05.757 --> 14:08.412
for this Alliance Science
Exchange thing --

14:08.456 --> 14:10.501
you know,
with the Civic Republic?

14:10.545 --> 14:13.896
I don't know where he is
or when he'll be back.

14:13.940 --> 14:17.030
My sister's mad at him
for going.

14:17.073 --> 14:19.989
I just miss him.

14:20.033 --> 14:24.298
Every family's got something,
right?

14:24.341 --> 14:27.779
♪♪

14:27.823 --> 14:31.479
Bye.

14:31.522 --> 14:41.489
♪♪

14:41.532 --> 14:50.672
♪♪

14:50.715 --> 14:54.632
[Walkers growling]

14:56.634 --> 15:06.601
♪♪

15:06.644 --> 15:16.437
♪♪

15:16.480 --> 15:21.964
♪♪

15:22.008 --> 15:26.229
[Pounding on door]

15:26.273 --> 15:28.536
♪♪

15:28.579 --> 15:30.755
Aah!

15:30.799 --> 15:32.540
[Growling]

15:32.583 --> 15:40.113
♪♪

15:40.156 --> 15:42.680
[Door closes]

15:42.724 --> 15:49.252
♪♪

15:49.296 --> 15:51.602
Alright.

15:51.646 --> 15:53.648
Let's see if it's working.

15:53.691 --> 15:54.997
[Grunts]

15:55.041 --> 15:57.521
Son of a mother...

16:01.395 --> 16:06.966
[Walkers growling]

16:07.009 --> 16:10.578
[Sighs]

16:10.621 --> 16:13.146
So, uh,
let me get this straight.

16:13.189 --> 16:16.540
She wants us to find her,
and then, all of a sudden,

16:16.584 --> 16:19.413
she just goes rogue and
runs kamikaze into The Blaze?

16:19.456 --> 16:20.762
Why?

16:20.805 --> 16:23.547
So we wouldn't have to.

16:23.591 --> 16:27.073
To spare me
the responsibility.

16:27.116 --> 16:29.989
I don't know what's going on
with her,

16:30.032 --> 16:33.253
but -- but what
she's doing now,

16:33.296 --> 16:35.820
it's not
just about Dad.

16:36.865 --> 16:43.045
I, uh --
I think I know why maybe.

16:44.829 --> 16:46.396
Well?

16:47.615 --> 16:50.183
At the tree house,

16:50.226 --> 16:53.403
that empty didn't go away
by itself.

16:53.447 --> 16:56.189
Hope led it away.

16:56.232 --> 16:59.061
She told me not to tell.

16:59.105 --> 17:00.802
Why?

17:00.845 --> 17:03.587
She, um --
She said something about

17:03.631 --> 17:07.374
our mistakes
shouldn't have to follow us.

17:07.417 --> 17:08.940
Okay.

17:08.984 --> 17:11.247
And what does that
have --

17:11.291 --> 17:14.076
'Cause sometimes our mistakes
follow us.

17:14.120 --> 17:17.427
Did Hope
say anything else?

17:17.471 --> 17:19.038
Uh, no.

17:19.081 --> 17:22.215
But I think she's done somethingshe feels bad about.

17:22.258 --> 17:23.825
Huck:
Why is that?

17:23.868 --> 17:27.046
♪♪

17:27.089 --> 17:29.178
Is thatwhat you're doing out here,

17:29.222 --> 17:31.833
trying to get awayfrom the things you done?

17:31.876 --> 17:33.139
Hey, Huck.

17:33.182 --> 17:43.149
♪♪

17:43.192 --> 17:46.935
♪♪

17:48.589 --> 17:50.852
Hey.

17:50.895 --> 17:53.159
I shouldn't have
come here.

17:53.202 --> 17:54.638
What?Why would you think --

17:54.682 --> 17:56.988
You have to be different,
strong.

17:57.032 --> 17:58.947
You are strong.

17:58.990 --> 18:02.472
Not in the way
I wanna be.

18:02.516 --> 18:06.259
What I am,
what I've done...

18:07.260 --> 18:10.915
...that's why
I shouldn't...

18:10.959 --> 18:13.440
That's why I can't...

18:13.483 --> 18:16.095
That's why
I didn't even...

18:16.138 --> 18:17.922
I-I'm sorry.

18:17.966 --> 18:19.663
Listen, my sister'sgoing through something,

18:19.707 --> 18:23.537
and I have no idea
what it is.

18:25.147 --> 18:28.281
I don't feel strong.

18:28.324 --> 18:31.371
I just want her
to be okay.

18:31.414 --> 18:36.593
I don't care about her mistakesor yours.

18:36.637 --> 18:37.855
♪♪

18:37.899 --> 18:40.336
You should.

18:40.380 --> 18:48.301
♪♪

18:48.344 --> 18:52.131
Silas,
what are you so afraid of?

18:52.174 --> 18:59.486
♪♪

18:59.529 --> 19:02.053
Me.

19:02.097 --> 19:04.882
I'm afraid of me.

19:04.926 --> 19:09.278
♪♪

19:09.322 --> 19:12.629
[ "Queen of Hearts"plays]

19:12.673 --> 19:20.159
♪♪

19:20.202 --> 19:22.726
♪ Sun rises above the factory

19:22.770 --> 19:25.512
♪ Rays don't make it
to the street ♪

19:25.555 --> 19:27.731
♪ Through the gate
come the employees ♪

19:27.775 --> 19:30.734
♪ Beat-down
and draggin' their feet ♪

19:30.778 --> 19:34.956
♪ Lefties handin' pamphlets,
workers comin' in ♪

19:34.999 --> 19:36.653
[Distorted]
♪ Lefties handin' --

19:36.697 --> 19:39.830
♪ On the pavement --

19:39.874 --> 19:43.443
[Tape whirs, clicks]

19:43.486 --> 19:45.532
[Indistinct conversations]

19:45.575 --> 19:48.056
Young man: Still can't believethey let him in here.Young woman: Right?

19:48.099 --> 19:50.711
Reason we got walls
is to keep the monsters out.

19:50.754 --> 19:54.193
[Echoing]
Monsters out.

19:54.236 --> 19:58.632
♪♪

20:07.597 --> 20:09.991
Silas?

20:10.034 --> 20:13.037
[Radio static]Hope: You guys there?

20:13.081 --> 20:14.778
Hope?
Hope, where are you?

20:14.822 --> 20:16.998
The good news is
I found the siren.

20:17.041 --> 20:19.348
What else?What's the bad news?

20:19.392 --> 20:21.263
Bad news is the crank
was broken,

20:21.307 --> 20:23.222
so, I, uh,
took the whole thing apart,

20:23.265 --> 20:25.311
and now, uh, I don't know
how to put it back together.

20:25.354 --> 20:27.008
How's your day?

20:27.051 --> 20:29.097
Well, there's someone
who would like to talk to you.

20:29.140 --> 20:31.708
Hope?
Where are you?

20:31.752 --> 20:34.276
Felix?
Is it just you?

20:34.320 --> 20:36.017
Huck's here, too.

20:36.060 --> 20:39.020
Now, Hope, tell me where you areso I can come and find you.

20:39.063 --> 20:41.414
No, no, I'm not putting you in
any more danger, okay?

20:41.457 --> 20:42.980
Just keep everyone safe,
alright?

20:43.024 --> 20:44.243
I got this.

20:44.286 --> 20:47.202
Hope, we're all here --all of us.

20:47.246 --> 20:48.638
Let us help you.

20:48.682 --> 20:50.031
[Radio static]

20:50.074 --> 20:51.815
Hope.

20:51.859 --> 20:54.688
The second I sound the siren,
it'll clear a path for you,

20:54.731 --> 20:56.429
but you need to haul a--

20:56.472 --> 20:57.734
[Radio static]What? Haul what?

20:57.778 --> 21:00.998
Ass! You need to haul ass
to the exit!

21:01.042 --> 21:02.913
Okay, well, I'm not veryfamiliar with that terminology,

21:02.957 --> 21:04.263
and with stakes
this high,

21:04.306 --> 21:06.003
I feel like we should beas clear as possible

21:06.047 --> 21:07.309
with what
we're trying to say here.Run, Elton.

21:07.353 --> 21:08.745
Just run to the exit.

21:08.789 --> 21:10.530
Okay?
I will meet you there.

21:10.573 --> 21:12.836
That way, Felix can chew me out
in person.

21:12.880 --> 21:15.839
Now, can you please
put my sister on?

21:15.883 --> 21:19.626
♪♪

21:19.669 --> 21:21.323
I'm here.

21:21.367 --> 21:22.846
♪♪

21:22.890 --> 21:24.413
[Sighs]

21:24.457 --> 21:28.765
You can do this -- like when
we were kids, remember?

21:28.809 --> 21:31.115
Listen.
I'm not mad.

21:31.159 --> 21:32.769
Just get
to the exit.

21:32.813 --> 21:34.467
I will.

21:34.510 --> 21:36.295
But if I don't --

21:36.338 --> 21:38.862
Hope, please.

21:38.906 --> 21:41.865
♪♪

21:41.909 --> 21:44.868
If I don't, promise you won'tcome back for me.

21:44.912 --> 21:47.088
I won't.

21:47.131 --> 21:49.612
Because I won't have to,

21:49.656 --> 21:52.354
because you're gonna
make it.

21:52.398 --> 21:54.878
♪♪

21:54.922 --> 21:56.271
I wish I hadn't had

21:56.315 --> 21:59.056
that stupid fight with Dadbefore he left.

21:59.100 --> 22:01.320
Look,I still want to find him,

22:01.363 --> 22:03.104
I want to see him.

22:03.147 --> 22:06.020
I just didn't think we'd beany good to him dead.

22:06.063 --> 22:07.891
I know.

22:07.935 --> 22:11.808
We are gonna
talk about it.

22:11.852 --> 22:14.507
We're gonna make it.

22:14.550 --> 22:16.683
Just haul your ass
to that exit,

22:16.726 --> 22:18.859
or I will
kill you myself.

22:18.902 --> 22:21.122
Got it.

22:21.165 --> 22:23.820
No goodbyes,
okay?

22:23.864 --> 22:27.346
♪♪

22:27.389 --> 22:29.783
No goodbyes.

22:29.826 --> 22:32.438
Are yougiving me the finger?

22:32.481 --> 22:35.702
Yeah.

22:35.745 --> 22:37.921
♪♪

22:37.965 --> 22:40.533
Cool.

22:40.576 --> 22:44.493
♪♪

22:44.537 --> 22:46.408
Haul ass.
Yeah, I got it now.

22:46.452 --> 22:47.801
Felix:
Oh, my God.

22:47.844 --> 22:56.157
♪♪

22:56.200 --> 22:58.725
Everybody get ready
to move.

22:58.768 --> 23:01.031
These will help
with the smoke.

23:01.075 --> 23:03.207
Lucky for you,
we brought extras.

23:03.251 --> 23:05.688
You take the lead,
I'll cover your six?

23:05.732 --> 23:06.950
Yeah.

23:06.994 --> 23:11.085
♪♪

23:11.128 --> 23:12.565
Silas.

23:12.608 --> 23:14.697
I-I don't think
I can.

23:14.741 --> 23:16.220
♪♪

23:16.264 --> 23:18.440
Well, I do.

23:18.484 --> 23:21.965
♪♪

23:22.009 --> 23:23.967
You can.

23:24.011 --> 23:33.977
♪♪

23:34.021 --> 23:35.718
♪♪

