[Birds chirping]

30:46.148 --> 30:54.896
♪♪

30:54.940 --> 30:56.376
♪♪

30:56.419 --> 31:00.467
[Reel clicking]

31:00.510 --> 31:10.477
♪♪

31:10.520 --> 31:20.226
♪♪

31:20.269 --> 31:22.881
[Sighs]

31:22.924 --> 31:25.448
You should've
come to me.

31:25.492 --> 31:27.059
Why?

31:27.102 --> 31:29.452
So you could try
and stop me?

31:29.496 --> 31:31.063
[Laughs]

31:31.106 --> 31:33.892
Isn't that
what you wanted?

31:36.111 --> 31:38.679
[Sighs]

31:38.722 --> 31:41.464
Think about
what you want.

31:41.508 --> 31:44.815
Your sister,
your friends,

31:44.859 --> 31:47.775
they're all
counting on you.

31:47.818 --> 31:57.437
♪♪

31:57.480 --> 32:07.447
♪♪

32:07.490 --> 32:11.103
♪♪

32:15.107 --> 32:16.325
[Water splashes softly]

32:16.369 --> 32:17.848
Daylight's burning.

32:17.892 --> 32:20.286
We should pack up,
get ready to hit the road.

32:20.329 --> 32:21.548
The road where?

32:21.591 --> 32:23.158
Oh, we're not going back
through that.

32:23.202 --> 32:26.118
And the other options on foot
aren't much better,

32:26.161 --> 32:28.816
so we cut up to Omaha,
resupply.

32:28.859 --> 32:30.339
The next transfer
to the University

32:30.383 --> 32:31.993
is in about two weeks.

32:32.037 --> 32:34.953
That's how we get back,
avoid The Blaze.

32:36.693 --> 32:39.914
Uh...

32:44.788 --> 32:47.313
I'm not going back.

32:48.357 --> 32:50.098
Me neither.

32:50.142 --> 32:52.535
You promised me
a fresh start.

32:52.579 --> 32:54.059
This is it.

32:54.102 --> 32:56.322
You know, your uncle's
worried sick about you.

32:56.365 --> 32:57.758
You know that,
right?

32:57.801 --> 32:59.325
Yeah, I...

32:59.368 --> 33:02.328
I miss him, too, but...

33:02.371 --> 33:05.374
I'm supposed to be
out here.

33:05.418 --> 33:10.031
I think he would want me to be
where I'm supposed to be.

33:11.598 --> 33:13.426
I'm where
I'm supposed to be, too.

33:13.469 --> 33:14.993
Great.

33:15.036 --> 33:16.385
Me too.

33:16.429 --> 33:18.170
If you want to keep your promiseto our dad,

33:18.213 --> 33:19.736
then you'll help us
find him.

33:19.780 --> 33:21.086
He's in New York.

33:21.129 --> 33:22.783
Lieutenant Colonel Kublekgave us the map.

33:22.826 --> 33:25.003
I know. But you're gonna
get yourselves killed.

33:25.046 --> 33:26.265
You realize that,
right?

33:26.308 --> 33:27.570
Now, you nearly did
back there.

33:27.614 --> 33:29.790
So come with us --
both of you.

33:29.833 --> 33:31.792
We're safer together.

33:31.835 --> 33:33.576
And you keep sayingthere's nothing you can do

33:33.620 --> 33:35.622
to help our dad,
but there is.

33:35.665 --> 33:37.406
You can help us
help him.

33:37.450 --> 33:39.234
Or don't.

33:39.278 --> 33:41.149
We're goingwith or without you.

33:42.194 --> 33:44.065
She's got a point.

33:44.109 --> 33:46.589
You know that,
right?

33:46.633 --> 33:50.028
There's no
turning 'em around --

33:50.071 --> 33:53.814
not right now,
at least.

33:53.857 --> 33:57.818
Keeping them safe
is all we can do...

33:57.861 --> 34:01.604
till there's something more
we can do.

34:01.648 --> 34:04.477
Yeah.

34:08.655 --> 34:11.136
[Sniffles]

34:11.179 --> 34:12.659
Hey.

34:12.702 --> 34:14.269
Hey.

34:17.098 --> 34:19.666
Thanks for having our backsback there.

34:21.189 --> 34:23.800
What changed?

34:23.844 --> 34:27.108
I guess I did.

34:27.152 --> 34:30.242
I was scared.

34:30.285 --> 34:33.114
I'm just tired
of being scared.

34:37.118 --> 34:39.860
Listen, Iris.

34:39.903 --> 34:43.951
There's something
I have to tell you.

34:47.476 --> 34:54.092
The night that Mom died,
it wasn't you.

34:54.135 --> 34:57.051
And it wasn't empties.

34:57.095 --> 34:59.140
And it wasn't people.

34:59.184 --> 35:01.708
It was me.

35:03.231 --> 35:06.452
Hope, what are you
talking about?

35:06.495 --> 35:07.844
I haven't told anyone,

35:07.888 --> 35:12.719
even after all these years,
not even Dad.

35:12.762 --> 35:18.594
The pregnant lady we saw
that night, she came back.

35:18.638 --> 35:20.857
And she had a gun.

35:20.901 --> 35:22.685
[Sniffles]

35:22.729 --> 35:25.297
She was freaked,
and I came at her,

35:25.340 --> 35:29.562
and -- and maybe if I'd done
nothing at all, she'd...

35:31.738 --> 35:33.131
She shot Mom.

35:33.174 --> 35:35.133
[Sniffles]

35:35.176 --> 35:37.787
I scared her,
and she shot Mom.

35:41.835 --> 35:44.490
I killed her.

35:44.533 --> 35:47.710
I shot her,
I picked up the gun,

35:47.754 --> 35:50.626
and it went off,
and I shot her.

35:50.670 --> 35:56.937
♪♪

35:56.980 --> 35:58.678
You should've told me.

35:58.721 --> 36:00.158
[Sniffles]

36:00.201 --> 36:02.769
I just didn't want what happenedto change you.

36:02.812 --> 36:07.513
I didn't want what happened
to change the way you saw me.

36:07.556 --> 36:09.254
But you're right.

36:09.297 --> 36:11.299
I should've told you.

36:11.343 --> 36:13.736
Yeah,
you should've.

36:13.780 --> 36:17.175
I knew there was somethingyou didn't tell me.

36:17.218 --> 36:24.965
♪♪

36:25.008 --> 36:28.534
That night...

36:28.577 --> 36:31.537
we were just kids.

36:31.580 --> 36:36.194
And the goddamn sky
was falling.

36:36.237 --> 36:38.326
We weren't ready
for it.

36:38.370 --> 36:40.372
None of us were
but...

36:40.415 --> 36:42.025
Iris,
I'm sorry.

36:42.069 --> 36:45.725
I'm so sorry.

36:45.768 --> 36:48.380
[Crying]

36:48.423 --> 36:51.034
[Sniffles]

36:51.078 --> 36:54.560
♪♪

36:54.603 --> 36:57.563
Okay.
It's okay.

36:57.606 --> 37:00.435
I know you are.

37:00.479 --> 37:02.568
[Sniffles]

37:02.611 --> 37:06.006
We're gonna
get through this.

37:06.049 --> 37:08.008
♪♪

37:08.051 --> 37:10.228
We kind of have to.

37:10.271 --> 37:12.752
[Sniffles]

37:12.795 --> 37:15.755
♪♪

37:15.798 --> 37:18.888
[Sniffles]

37:18.932 --> 37:21.543
Come on.

37:21.587 --> 37:24.677
[Sniffles]

37:24.720 --> 37:26.766
[Clears throat]

37:26.809 --> 37:31.423
♪♪

37:31.466 --> 37:34.208
Look,
we should go to Omaha.

37:34.252 --> 37:37.907
That's where safety is,
and your dad wants you safe --

37:37.951 --> 37:41.650
not that either of you seem
to care about that at all.

37:41.694 --> 37:45.001
Look,
this is a mistake, okay?

37:45.045 --> 37:47.090
You're gonna see it.

37:47.134 --> 37:49.049
I just hope to God it doesn't
take one of you getting hurt

37:49.092 --> 37:51.399
or worse
before that happens.

37:51.443 --> 37:53.619
Are you trying say
you're coming with us?

37:53.662 --> 37:55.403
Are you giving me
an option?Not really.

37:55.447 --> 37:56.839
Then I guess
that's what I'm saying --

37:56.883 --> 37:59.146
at least
until I can convince you two

37:59.189 --> 38:01.366
to just turn around and go back,which I will.

38:01.409 --> 38:04.194
Cool.
Yeah.

38:05.239 --> 38:06.545
For what it's worth,

38:06.588 --> 38:08.895
I'm sorryI dragged you into this.

38:08.938 --> 38:11.201
But I'm kind of glad
you're here.

38:11.245 --> 38:12.638
Well...

38:12.681 --> 38:14.857
that makes one of us.

38:14.901 --> 38:19.297
And I'm sorry for stealingyour jacket -- and Will's...

38:19.340 --> 38:20.646
I mean...

38:20.689 --> 38:23.431
...even though they lookreally good on us.

38:23.475 --> 38:24.998
Aw. Mm.

38:25.041 --> 38:27.305
Nah, they totally look better
on me and Will.

38:27.348 --> 38:30.438
Yeah, no.

38:30.482 --> 38:32.092
♪♪

38:32.135 --> 38:35.008
Go!

38:35.051 --> 38:42.320
♪♪

38:42.363 --> 38:44.887
Hey.

38:44.931 --> 38:47.325
So, uh,we ever gonna talk about

38:47.368 --> 38:48.891
why you wentback inside the devil's asshole

38:48.935 --> 38:50.763
to save some luggage?
[Chuckles]

38:50.806 --> 38:53.679
It was to save
my mom's manuscript.

38:53.722 --> 38:56.682
She never finished
the last chapter,

38:56.725 --> 39:00.686
so I want to --
for her, but for me, too.

39:00.729 --> 39:03.384
I know it was kind of irrationalgoing in there.

39:03.428 --> 39:04.646
It was.

39:04.690 --> 39:07.606
But it was also
kind of badass.

39:07.649 --> 39:09.521
Oh.

39:09.564 --> 39:12.219
Grandfather: Silas,
Pastor Ridgway said something

39:12.262 --> 39:13.873
in church this morning
that stuck.

39:13.916 --> 39:15.744
It was a passage from Isaiah.

39:15.788 --> 39:18.051
He said, "God is great.

39:18.094 --> 39:20.314
He does not faint
or grow weary;

39:20.358 --> 39:23.926
his understanding
is unsearchable.

39:23.970 --> 39:27.147
I think that means
that even with, well,

39:27.190 --> 39:30.542
the hardest people,
the people with problems,

39:30.585 --> 39:32.065
God loves them.

39:32.108 --> 39:34.720
He does not give up on them.

39:34.763 --> 39:36.635
Hey.

39:36.678 --> 39:41.509
♪♪

39:41.553 --> 39:44.251
[Birds chirping]

39:44.294 --> 39:53.739
♪♪

39:53.782 --> 40:03.313
♪♪

40:03.357 --> 40:05.185
Grandmother:
We love you, Silas.

40:05.228 --> 40:08.493
We're so lucky
to be your grandparents.

40:08.536 --> 40:13.498
Life isn't easy, kiddo,
but it's good.

40:13.541 --> 40:15.978
We make it good.

40:27.642 --> 40:29.252
[Knock on door]

40:29.296 --> 40:31.777
Barca:
Lieutenant Colonel?

40:31.820 --> 40:34.910
Sergeant Major Barca.

40:36.956 --> 40:38.871
You're off base.

40:38.914 --> 40:40.307
It's late.

40:40.350 --> 40:42.004
I'm due back.

